      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes, it is deterministic. I am not sure what you mean. Currently there is no easy way to update Ready when an included invocation is finalized, as we talked offline. We have two choices: \n1) allow NULL and use NULL as \"this value may be stale\"\n2) add an index (IncludedInvocationId, InvocatoinId) and whenever an included invocation is being finalized, also *incoming* edges.\n\nI am OK with both. \nThere is a chance that we may need to find incoming edges in the future too. Also it will probably simplify all code that deals with Ready column. \nAlso option (2) is possible largely because we use spanner, where transactions are not limited to one entity group, so maybe we should use this ability.\n\nWDYT?",
